{
  "ComponentID": "IP5306",
  "ComponentType": "Integrated Power Management SOC (System-on-Chip) for Power Banks",
  "Description": "The IP5306 is a highly integrated power management SOC that combines a synchronous boost converter, lithium-ion battery charging management, and battery level indication into a single chip, providing a complete power solution for mobile power banks. It features synchronous switching for both charging (up to 2.1A) and discharging/boosting (up to 2.4A), supports simultaneous charging and discharging via built-in power path management, and drives 1-4 LEDs for battery level display. It includes a button control for power-on and flashlight driving, automatic load detection for entering low-power standby, and requires only a single external inductor.",
